summary:
- **Positive Phase I Clinical Trial Results**:  
  - No dose-limiting safety signals observed; Xolatryp™ well tolerated in all six cohorts.  
  - Topline results expected in **September 2025 quarter**.  
  - Phase IIa trial in acute myocardial infarction (STEMI) patients planned for **early 2026**.  

- **Preclinical Efficacy**:  
  - Xolatryp demonstrated **42% cardioprotection** (3-hour dosing) and reduced arrhythmias in coronary heart disease models.  
  - Statistically significant neuroprotective effects in **traumatic brain injury** and **stroke models**.  

No capital markets or liquidity-impacting actions announced. Focus remains on clinical milestones.
